Debswana of Botswana Sees 4.6% Increase in 2011 Diamond Production

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-05-24T18:05:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/debswana-of-botswana-sees-4-6-increase-in-2011-diamond-production.html
Debswana Diamond Co., a joint venture
between the Botswana government and  De Beers , plans to increase
diamond production by 4.6 percent to 25 million carats this
year, said Managing Director Jim Gowans.  The company has sold $1.1 billion of the gems so far, he
said today at a meeting in Gaborone, the capital. In 2009,
Debswana mined 23.9 million carats that were sold for $2.6
billion, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  